{
  "texts": [
    "Max pooling is more likely to memorize as it preserves only the strongest feature in each window that may not represent the entire window.",
    "On the other hand, average pooling considers all features in each window, which can help preserve more information.",
    "Additionally, average pooling can help smooth out the output, which can be useful when the input is noisy or volatile.",
    "In this context, the changes we made are given in Fig. 7.",
    "It has been observed that this improvement has a positive effect on detection performance.The architecture of YOLOv7-AP-CBAM obtained with the updates made in the YOLOv7 architecture was used in the numbering of teeth and in the detection of caries."
  ]
}